Pre-Game Insights: Australia look to fine-tune their performance ahead of the semi-final against South Africa.
Bangladesh are fighting to qualify for the Champions Trophy and have suffered off-field turmoil with coach changes.
Steven Smith is likely to return for Australia, while Shakib Al Hasan is ruled out for Bangladesh due to injury.
The match is the first ODI between Australia and Bangladesh since 2019.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Maharashtra Cricket Association surface is batting-friendly with scores over 330 common.
Warm and sunny conditions are expected, with a maximum temperature of 32 degrees Celsius.
